n_samp = 250

sim_df_const = 
  tibble(
    x = rnorm(n_samp, 1, 1),
    error = rnorm(n_samp, 0, 1),
    y = 2 + 3 * x + error
  )

sim_df_nonconst = sim_df_const %>% 
  mutate(
  error = error * .75 * x,
  y = 2 + 3 * x + error
)
sim_df = 
  bind_rows(const = sim_df_const, nonconst = sim_df_nonconst, .id = "data_source") 

sim_df %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = .5) +
  stat_smooth(method = "lm") +
  facet_grid(~data_source)

Fit two models

sim_df_const %>% 
  lm(y ~ x,data = .) %>% 
  broom::tidy() # 
## # A tibble: 2 x 5
##   term        estimate std.error statistic   p.value
##   <chr>          <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>     <dbl>
## 1 (Intercept)     1.98    0.0981      20.2 3.65e- 54
## 2 x               3.04    0.0699      43.5 3.84e-118
boot_sample = function(df) {
  sample_frac(df,size = 1, replace = TRUE) # allow replacement 
}

boot_sample(sim_df_nonconst) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x, y = y)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = .5) + # point darker appear more than one time #
  stat_smooth(method = "lm")

Oranize a dataframe

boot_straps = 
  data_frame(
    strap_number = 1:1000,
    strap_sample = rerun(1000, boot_sample(sim_df_nonconst))
  )
## Warning: `data_frame()` is deprecated, use `tibble()`.
## This warning is displayed once per session.

Do some kind of analysis

boot_straps_result = boot_straps %>% 
  mutate(models = map(strap_sample,~lm(y ~ x,data = .x)),
         results = map(models,broom::tidy)) %>% 
  select(-strap_sample,-models) %>% 
  unnest(results)

Concern about the slope Summarize these results

boot_straps_result %>% 
  group_by(term) %>% 
  summarize(se = sd(estimate))
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   term            se

## 2 x           0.101

Try the modelr package

sim_straps = 
    sim_df_nonconst %>% 
    modelr::bootstrap(1000)
sim_df_const %>% 
  modelr::bootstrap(n = 1000) %>% 
  mutate(models = map(strap, ~lm(y ~ x, data = .x) ),
         results = map(models, broom::tidy)) %>% 
  select(-strap, -models) %>% 
  unnest(results) %>% 
  group_by(term) %>% 
  summarize(boot_se = sd(estimate))
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   term        boot_se
##   <chr>         <dbl>
## 1 (Intercept)  0.0985
## 2 x            0.0697

Airbnb data

data("nyc_airbnb")

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  mutate(stars = review_scores_location / 2) %>% 
  rename(
    boro = neighbourhood_group,
    neighborhood = neighbourhood) %>% 
  filter(boro != "Staten Island") %>% 
  select(price, stars, boro, neighborhood, room_type)
nyc_airbnb %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = stars, y = price, color = room_type)) + 
  geom_point()
